          "tz": -420
        },
        "subject": "LU-549 xattr: packaged xattr in single RPC reply",
        "message": "LU-549 xattr: packaged xattr in single RPC reply\n\nCurrently, MDS returns ACL together with other object's attributes\nwhen replies getattr/lookup RPC. As for stating directory object,\nclient will send additional RPC for default ACL.\n\nAs an improvement, MDS will return packaged xattr to contain both\nposix ACL and default ACL (for directory). For remote client, the\nremote permission is also returned through packaged xattr.\n\nThe packaged xattr framework supports to return more other xattrs\nby single RPC.\n\nSigned-off-by: James Simmons <uja.ornl@gmail.com>\nSigned-off-by: Fan Yong <yong.fan@whamcloud.com>\nSigned-off-by: Bob Glossman <bogl@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: Ic12bdef6b0174603e244af2384f72cb5142f1150\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/b2_1"
    }
